ized form of Gaelic <b>Ó hOistín</b> ‘descendant of <i>Oistín</i>’, the Gaelic form of the personal name <i>Augustine</i> (see   Austin  )."]}]},{"name":"Zebulon","type":"FIRST","meanings":["Hebrew: Dwelling habitation."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705197,"age":53,"year":"1455","julianDay":2252488,"title":"Wars of the Roses","description":"Wars of the Roses was a series of English civil wars for control of the throne of England between the royal families House of Lancaster and the House of York. The name of the war was derived as the red rose was the symbol of the Lancastrians and the white rose was the symbol of the Yorks.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/british-history/wars-of-the-roses","urlTitle":"History - Wars of the Roses","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"When Sir Zebulon Heston III was born in 1402, in Yorkshire, England, his father, Zebulon Heston, was 25 and his mother, Dorothy Hutchinson, was 22. He had at least 1 daughter with Lady Elizabeth Buckman. He died in 1476, in his hometown, at the age of 74."},"et":{"1402–1476":"1402–1476","1409–1493":"1409–1493","1465–1540":"1465–1540","1377–1402":"1377–1402","1380–1402":"1380–1402","1402":"1402","1455":"1455","1465":"1465","1476":"1476","1377":"1377","1540":"1540","1493":"1493","1409":"1409","1380":"1380","Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, England","Gildersome, Yorkshire, England":"Gildersome, Yorkshire, England","London, England":"London, England"},"fi":{"1402–1476":"1402–1476","1409–1493":"1409–1493","1465–1540":"1465–1540","1377–1402":"1377–1402","1380–1402":"1380–1402","1402":"1402","1455":"1455","1465":"1465","1476":"1476","1377":"1377","1540":"1540","1493":"1493","1409":"1409","1380":"1380","Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, England","Gildersome, Yorkshire, England":"Gildersome, Yorkshire, England","London, England":"London, England"},"fr":{"1402–1476":"1402–1476","1409–1493":"1409–1493","1465–1540":"1465–1540","1377–1402":"1377–1402","1380–1402":"1380–1402","1402":"1402","1455":"